Hey folks, long time no update (cry some moar). Hows things?

For me, Great, thanks for not asking, or contacting me or giving damn. I love you too.

Been playing muchos Games lately, enjoying the good life one might say.

Finished FF7 again a few months back, maxxed it, proud of myself ya know :)

Finished smash bros brawl the other day, 7/10 on the story mode, it was good. cutscenes were awesome, but ya know, its a fightan game, what did you expect.

Playing FF11 again, religously almost. Really powering on this time. Getting shit done and enjoying more than i ever have.

Aside from that, music stufffss, panic at the discos new single is quite good, i like it anyhow...

And ive started listening to a new band called "new years day" they are pretty good.... in my opinion...

I need more new music, reccomendations anyone? (im looking at you sarri >_> )

need a job now, soon, whenever. 

Waking up at 5:30am 5 days awake to spend more time with kat makes me feel like a good boyfriend, cause i fucking am. Breakfast in bed every day for her, at 5:30 am.

Did i mention 5:30 am.

AM

MORNING

...

Kats sister is coming today for the weekend and is having the back room, my PC is in the back room. So i'm moving it to the front room. I cant honestly be up till 3am with a 12 year old in the room sleeping. and i dont fancy working my own schedule around others, even if my schedule is just "chat and play games with dicky until to tired to move" 

yay Supreme Commander. Its getting to easy. Which is saying something. Considering the AI is set to "Cheating" and it really fucking does cheat. Its just.. really easy to win :/

Fight club, hmm yeah...

So im like what, 8 years fucking late, gimme a break.

Just watched this movie. I like, I like the psychology in it, of society. It's clever.

Plot was... somewhat predictable, it became faily obvious that he was tyler when he started sleeping with marla or whatever that crack whores name was (fuck me was she rough on the eyes).

I think the placebo song at the end was a nice touch.

But yeah, i liked the theme of film, i liked the way it was present, and i liked the characters.

I'm glad i saw this now for the first time and not yonks ago when it came out. I wouldn't of been able to grasp the outlook it presents.

Society polices itself. and im not talking about crime per-say, you know what im talking fucking psychological shit on live journal, you dont deserve that. take that how you will.

its 6:33am.

I'm Tired.

I Can't sleep.

I see kat today, im looking forward to that alot, its been 3 days and i need my fix, i need to be around her. she makes life so much better :D

you may have noticed me and kat are moving in together soon, probably september when uni is almost upon us again.

I like my life. I enjoy it, there are pressures, but they are a neccesity. Without the bad you cannot distinguish the good.
Almost all is well. I wish i could see more of you more often though.

Keep well guys, i'll no doubt update again in about 2 months.
By then i should be updating from liverpool again. In a flat i'll be sharing the lady whom I am in love with.
A flat that isnt student accomdation, A Flat that is Rented, a flat that is for me and for her. For however many years we are in liverpool. That place will be home.

I wont "return home" for the summer. I will already be home.

That scares me a little. Moving to uni, wasnt really moving at all. I was going to a place that was what i always wanted my own bedroom to be. Multipurpose. My single room Studio Room at liverpool. A Kitchen a bedroom a living space. Everything.

But THIS. this isnt moving to uni. This is bigger. This is Moving to Liverpool. Moving to a new home. A home that i can call my own.no.... Our home.

This last year i have grown up alot. Things have changed for the better.I feel im finally moving into that big, wide world.

its freaking 7:06 am now, i drifted to sleep a little, well enough rantage, i'll post what ive written up until now and i hope i didnt make an ass of myself :D
